      • handshake

                                boolean allowExtensions,
                                int idleTimeout,
                                io.netty.handler.codec.http.HttpHeaders responseHeaders)
        Complete the handshake of a given request. The connection will be timed out if the connection is idle for given time period.
        Parameters:
        subProtocols - Sub-Protocols which are allowed by the service.
        allowExtensions - whether the extensions are allowed or not.
        idleTimeout - Idle timeout in milli-seconds for WebSocket connection.
        responseHeaders - Extra headers to add to the handshake response or null if no extra headers should be added
        Returns:
        the handshake future.

      • handshake

        ServerHandshakeFuture handshake(String[] subProtocols,
                                boolean allowExtensions,
                                int idleTimeout,
                                io.netty.handler.codec.http.HttpHeaders responseHeaders,
                                int maxFramePayloadLength)
        Complete the handshake of a given request. The connection will be timed out if the connection is idle for given time period.
        Parameters:
        subProtocols - Sub-Protocols which are allowed by the service.
        allowExtensions - whether the extensions are allowed or not.
        idleTimeout - Idle timeout in milli-seconds for WebSocket connection.
        responseHeaders - Extra headers to add to the handshake response or null if no extra headers should be added.
        maxFramePayloadLength - Maximum allowable frame payload length. Setting this value to your application's requirement may reduce denial of service attacks using long data frames.
        Returns:
        the handshake future.
